# CSS Variables

CSS Variables help reuse values throughout a stylesheet.

## Creating Variables

```css
:root {
    --primary-color: #007bff;
    --secondary-color: #28a745;
}
```

## Using Variables

```css
button {
    background-color: var(--primary-color);
}
```

## Multiple Variables

```css
:root {
    --font-size: 16px;
    --border-radius: 8px;
}
```

## Benefits

- Easy maintenance
- Consistent design
- Faster updates

## Real-World Example

Large applications use variables for branding consistency.

## Summary

CSS Variables improve scalability and maintainability.
